i%2C%20to%20the%20Vithoba%20temple%20in%20Pandharpur.%20There%20are%2C%20literally%2C%20thousands%20of%20temples%20across%20India%20%E2%80%93%20big%2C%20small%2C%20ancient%2C%20recent%20%E2%80%93%20dedicated%20to%20scores%20of%20Indian%20gods%20and%20goddesses%2C%20and%20crores%20of%20devout%20Hindus%20go%20to%20these%20temples%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20these%20the%20crores%20of%20Hindus%20who%20have%20allegedly%20lost%20their%20way%3F%20No.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrores%20of%20Hindu%20shopkeepers%20dedicate%20a%20little%20alcove%20to%20their%20preferred%20deity%20even%20in%20the%20tiniest%20of%20shops%2C%20and%20the%20day%E2%80%99s%20work%20begins%20with%20a%20prayer%20and%20the%20ritual%20tinkling%20of%20a%20bell.%20Crores%20of%20Hindus%20have%20%E2%80%98mandirs%E2%80%99%20in%20their%20homes%20%E2%80%93%20some%20modest%2C%20some%20grand%20%E2%80%93%20and%20there%20too%2C%20the%20average%20Hindu%20family%20performs%20regular%20%E2%80%98aarti%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98puja%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20these%20the%20Hindus%20who%20have%20lost%20touch%20with%20their%20religion%3F%20No.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESorry%2C%20Hindus%20have%20not%20%E2%80%98lost%E2%80%99%20their%20way%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrores%20of%20Hindus%20follow%20the%20rituals%20laid%20down%20for%20key%20moments%20of%20a%20Hindu%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20such%20as%20the%20birth%20and%20naming%20of%20a%20child%2C%20marriage%2C%20the%20entry%20into%20a%20new%20home%2C%20and%20death%2C%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20these%20not%20practising%2C%20god-fearing%20Hindus%3F%20Yes%2C%20they%20most%20certainly%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20then%2C%20where%20are%20the%20%E2%80%98lost%E2%80%99%20Hindus%20that%20need%20%E2%80%98re-awakening%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98de-colonising%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ram%20Mandir%20in%20Ayodhya%20has%20been%20a%20well-executed%2C%20well-milked%20political%20project.%20The%20idea%20being%20to%20harvest%20votes%20from%20a%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98resurgent%E2%80%99%20Hindu%20pride%2C%20derived%20from%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20grand%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20allowing%20all%20the%20credit%20to%20accrue%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20hoping%20it%20translates%20into%20a%20win%20in%20the%20General%20Election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20problem%20is%2C%20the%20whole%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Fbooks%2Fessay-media-religious-conversion%5C%22%3Enarrative%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fwhy-its-crucial-to-understand-that-hindu-pride-goes-beyond-the-modi-factor%5C%22%3Eof%20%E2%80%98lost%E2%80%99%20Hindus%20and%20%E2%80%98hurt%E2%80%99%20pride%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20false%20construct.%20Simply%20put%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Hindus%20are%20neither%20%E2%80%98lost%E2%80%99%20nor%20%E2%80%98hurt%E2%80%99.%20Their%20pride%20and%20their%20faith%20is%20pretty%20intact%20too.%20Every%20political%20party%20and%20its%20ideologues%20and%20its%20intellectual%20supporters%20may%20put%20a%20%E2%80%98deeper%E2%80%99%20spin%20on%20any%20political%20gimmick%20they%20roll%20out.%20But%20they%20should%20not%20start%20believing%20their%20own%20spin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERam%20Mandir%20hype%20is%20%E2%80%98pseudo-religosity%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20the%20Congress%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress%20were%20accused%20of%20practising%20%E2%80%98minority-appeasement%E2%80%99%20politics%20and%20labelled%20%E2%80%98pseudo-secular.%E2%80%99%20Today%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98majority%20appeasement%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20culminated%20in%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20accompanied%20by%20hyped-up%20%E2%80%98pseudo-religiosity%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98pseudo-spiritual-reawakening%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devout%20are%20welcome%20to%20jet%20into%20Ayodhya%2C%20stay%20at%20a%20swanky%20hotel%2C%20and%20get%20a%20%E2%80%98darshan%E2%80%99%20at%20the%20grand%20mandir.%20But%20just%20as%20intrinsically%20Hindu%20is%20the%20long%20trek%20to%20the%20Amarnath%20cave%20or%20Kedarnath%20or%20Gangotri%20Dham%2C%20or%20to%20the%20Vaishno%20Devi%20mandir%2C%20and%20then%20getting%20darshan%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98deity%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20the%20arduous%20nature%20of%20the%20journey%20that%20makes%20it%20a%20test%20of%20the%20pilgrim%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98faith%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20crores%20of%20Indians%20have%20been%20passing%20this%20test%20for%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20may%20well%20add%20the%20new%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Mandir%20to%20their%20bucket%20list%2C%20but%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20make%20them%20any%20more%20Hindu%2C%20or%20any%20more%20aware%20of%20their%20Hindu%20identity%2C%20than%20they%20already%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22212245%2Fimage-1784.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22212245%2Fimage-1784.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22212245%2Fimage-1784-300x130.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22212245%2Fimage-1784-1024x442.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694054%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERam%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya.%20Photo%3A%20Screenshot%20from%20DD%20News%20broadcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmodi-governments-campaign-around-ram-mandir-negates-everything-that-india-stands-for%5C%22%3EModi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Campaign%20Around%20Ram%20Mandir%20Negates%20Everything%20That%20India%20Stands%20For%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%20see%20how%20Hinduism%20thrives%2C%20come%20to%20the%20Kumbh%20Mela%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20also%20briefly%20discuss%20the%20Kumbh%20Mela.%20On%20February%204%2C%202019%2C%20over%2024%20crore%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fa-record-over-24-crore-people-visited-kumbh-2019-more-than-total-tourists-in-up-in-2014-17%2Fstory-9uncpmhBPnBj11ClnTiYQP.html%5C%22%3Eattended%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Ardh%20Kumbh%20Mela%20at%20Prayagraj%2C%20marking%20the%20highest%20attendance%20ever%20on%20a%20single%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kumbh%20Mela%20stands%20as%20a%20breathtaking%20testament%20to%20mass%20faith%20in%20practice%2C%20spanning%20centuries.%20Its%20roots%20extend%20back%20to%20ancient%20times%2C%20with%20mentions%20in%20the%20Rig%20Veda%20(1500%20BCE)%20and%20early%20Puranas.%20In%20644%20CE%2C%20the%20Buddhist%20Chinese%20traveler%20Hiuen%20Tsang%2C%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20King%20Harsha%E2%80%99s%20Prayag%2C%20provided%20an%20account%20of%20the%20Kumbh%20Mela.%20Abul%20Fazl%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Ain-i-Akbari%2C%E2%80%99%20written%20in%201590%2C%20also%20details%20the%20Kumbha%20or%20Magha%20Mela%2C%20as%20it%20was%20commonly%20referred%20to%20then.%20Munshi%20Sujan%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKhulasat-ut-Tawarikh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20written%20in%201695%2C%20chronicles%20multiple%20Kumbh%20Melas%20at%20Haridwar%2C%20Trimbak%20(near%20Nashik%2C%20at%20the%20source%20of%20the%20Godavari%20River)%2C%20and%20Prayag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20crores%20of%20Hindus%20have%20actively%20participated%20in%20the%20Kumbh%20Melas.%20This%20tradition%20did%20not%20halt%20or%20stutter%20even%20during%20the%20years%20of%20Mughal%20rule%20and%20the%20British%20Raj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fa-lesson-on-temples-from-swami-vivekananda%5C%22%3EA%20Lesson%20on%20Temples%20From%20Swami%20Vivekananda%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERam%20Mandir%20inauguration%2C%20a%20political%20event%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ram%20Mandir%20campaign%2C%20the%20build%20up%20on%20social%20media%2C%20the%20intertwining%20of%20it%20with%20the%20Modi%20cult%2C%20the%20raucous%20nature%20of%20it%2C%20the%20merchandising%20of%20it%2C%20the%20face-paint%2C%20the%20flags%2C%20the%20roping%20in%20of%20Bollywood%20celebs%20as%20amplifiers%20of%20the%20event%20%E2%80%93%20made%20it%20far%20more%20similar%20to%20a%20jamboree%20like%20the%20Indian%20Premier%20League.%20A%20new%20mandir%20does%20not%20need%20the%20build-up%20that%20comes%20before%20a%20major%20Bollywood%20film.%20So%20why%20were%20we%20subjected%20to%20all%20the%20hype%3F%20Because%2C%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20was%20a%20political%20event.%20It%20was%20the%20culmination%20of%20a%20political%20campaign%20that%20had%20to%20be%20seriously%20played%20up.%20And%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20my%20quick%20uttering%20of%20the%20Gayatri%20Mantra%20at%20home%2C%20my%20visit%20to%20the%20neighbourhood%20mandir%2C%20my%20trip%20to%20Haridwar%20with%20the%20ashes%20of%20my%20grandparent%2C%20even%20mass%20events%20like%20the%20Kumbh%2C%20or%20the%20daily%20churn%20of%20the%20faithful%20that%20we%20see%20on%20the%20ghats%20of%20Varanasi%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20are%20deeply%20personal%20spiritual%20acts%20and%20journeys%2C%20for%20all%20practicing%20Hindus.%20It%20does%20not%20require%20hype%20to%20urge%20me%20or%20any%20other%20Hindu%20to%20do%20any%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20also%20examine%20the%20argument%20about%20how%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20will%20%E2%80%98decolonise%E2%80%99%20the%20Hindu%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20already%20described%20how%20Hindus%20have%20steadily%20practiced%20their%20faith%20over%20the%20centuries%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20medieval%20despot%20who%20ran%20their%20lives%20at%20any%20given%20time%2C%20some%20kind%2C%20some%20cruel%2C%20some%20self-serving%2C%20Hindu%2C%20Christian%20and%20Muslim%20alike.%20For%20most%20Hindus%2C%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20their%20religion%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20need%20any%20decolonising%20when%20India%20achieved%20independence%20in%201947.%20There%20was%20no%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98religious%20inferiority%E2%80%99%20to%20shrug%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20Satyagraha%20%E2%80%98decolonised%E2%80%99%20the%20Indian%20mind%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20needed%20was%20mass%20political%20emancipation%2C%20and%20in%20the%2030%20years%20preceding%201947%2C%20that%20push%20came%20from%20Gandhi.%20His%20unique%20mobilisation%20of%20crores%20of%20Indians%20to%20participate%20in%20non-violent%20protest%20and%20resistance%20made%20each%20of%20them%20a%20stakeholder%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20facilitated%20a%20mass%20shedding%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20mindset.%20Thousands%20of%20freedom%20fighters%20went%20to%20jail%2C%20hundreds%20were%20beaten%20in%20lathi%20charges%2C%20and%20hundreds%20were%20killed%20%E2%80%93%20an%20unprecedented%20number%20of%20Indians%20were%20invested%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom%2C%20and%20they%20remained%20invested%20even%20after%20August%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20mind%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20our%20fledgling%20democracy%20did%20not%20unravel%20like%20that%20of%20many%20countries%20that%20emerged%20from%20colonialism.%20A%20young%20nation%20would%20not%20have%20grown%20from%20strength%20to%20strength%20as%20a%20democracy%20if%20it%20had%20not%20decisively%20broken%20away%20from%20its%20colonial%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20BJP%20wants%20to%20break%20away%20from%20is%20not%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98colonial%E2%80%99%20past%2C%20but%20its%20post-colonial%20%E2%80%98Nehruvian%E2%80%99%20past.%20The%20aversion%20to%20Nehru%2C%20and%20a%20more%20discreet%20aversion%20to%20Gandhi%2C%20is%20present%20simply%20because%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20need%20to%20%E2%80%98clear%20the%20shelf%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20earlier%20icons%20and%20make%20room%20for%20their%20own.%20But%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20that%20without%20attacking%20them%20and%20their%20contributions%20and%20accusing%20them%20of%20failing%20to%20rid%20India%20of%20its%20%E2%80%98colonial%20mindset.%E2%80%99%20India%20did%20shed%20its%20British%20past%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%2C%20in%20mind%2C%20spirit%2C%20and%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%5C%22%3EAyodhya%3A%20Once%20There%20Was%20a%20Mosque%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98superpower%E2%80%99%20moment%20came%20before%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20even%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20sounding%20a%20bit%20simplistically%20ra-ra-ish%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20ask%3A%20Did%20India%20wait%20for%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20before%20becoming%20a%20nuclear%20power%20complete%20with%20warheads%3F%20Did%20India%20need%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20to%20motivate%20it%20to%20become%20a%20leader%20in%20space%20exploration%20or%20to%20have%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20defence%20forces%3F%20Did%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20propel%20India%20to%20become%20the%20fifth%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%3F%20For%20decades%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20massive%20%E2%80%98soft%E2%80%99%20power%20has%20grown%20organically%20(unlike%20the%20heavily%20%E2%80%98marketed%E2%80%99%20soft%20power%20of%20the%20US)%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20diaspora%2C%20its%20cinema%2C%20its%20cricket%2C%20its%20food%2C%20its%20music%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20India%20does%20not%20need%20to%20shake%20off%20any%20imaginary%20vestiges%20of%20any%20imaginary%20colonial%20hangover.%20It%20was%20all%20done%20and%20dusted%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20call%20out%20the%20%E2%80%98pseudo-religious%E2%80%99%20nature%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20political%20campaign%20and%20understand%20it%20for%20what%20it%20really%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frohit-khanna%5C%22%3ERohit%20Khanna%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20video%20storyteller.%20He%20has%20been%20managing%20editor%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Quint%3Cem%3E%2C%20and%20is%20a%20two-time%20Ramnath%20Goenka%20Award%20winner.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706874802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22185025%2FScreenshot-2024-01-22-at-12.41.27-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhindus-havent-lost-their-way-unveiling-the-pseudo-religiosity-behind-the-ram-mandir-campaign%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Just%20as%20intrinsically%20Hindu%20is%20the%20long%20trek%20to%20the%20Amarnath%20cave%20or%20Kedarnath%20or%20Gangotri%20Dham%2C%20or%20to%20the%20Vaishno%20Devi%20mandir.%20The%20devotees%20may%20well%20add%20the%20new%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20Mandir%20to%20their%20bucket%20list%2C%20but%20it%20won't%20make%20them%20any%20more%20Hindu%20than%20they%20already%20are.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhindus-havent-lost-their-way-unveiling-the-pseudo-religiosity-behind-the-ram-mandir-campaign%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222nd%20Test%3A%20Jaiswal%20ton%20takes%20India%20to%20336%2F6%20on%20Day%201%20vs%20England%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706873500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107363920%2Cimgsize-51442.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fengland-