-695345%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221040%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20images%20courtesy%20of%20Khudai%20Khidmatgar.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706858766000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02120144%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-11.57.20%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fin-photos-a-demolished-slum-in-jasola%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Residents%20are%20now%20left%20in%20the%20open%20with%20the%20rains%20having%20worsened%20the%20situation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fin-photos-a-demolished-slum-in-jasola%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20a%20First%2C%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20End%20Without%20a%20Deputy%20Speaker%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02121753%2FGFGx-CPbAAAB7us-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20be%20the%20first%20to%20conclude%20its%20tenure%20without%20a%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20in%20a%20development%20that%20has%20been%20called%20%E2%80%9Cundemocratic%E2%80%9D%20by%20opposition%20parliamentarians%20and%20unprecedented%20by%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2010-day%20interim%20budget%20session%20which%20started%20on%20January%2031%20is%20the%20last%20sitting%20of%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20before%20it%20is%20adjourned%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20in%20April-May%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general%20P.D.T.%20Achary%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20has%20never%20been%20a%20situation%20barring%20the%20present%20instance%2C%20where%20there%20has%20been%20no%20deputy%20speaker%20for%20the%20entire%20tenure%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20quite%20unlikely%20that%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20will%20be%20chosen%20by%20the%20house%20now.%20And%20there%20is%20no%20point%20now%20either.%20Deputy%20speaker%20is%20chosen%20along%20with%20the%20speaker%20and%20the%20practice%20has%20been%20to%20elect%20the%20speaker%20first%20and%20within%20a%20week%E2%80%99s%20time%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20will%20also%20be%20elected.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchary%20said%20that%20when%20it%20is%20a%20constitutionally%20mandated%20provision%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20adhered%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20a%20mandatory%20provision%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20House%20has%20to%20abide%20by%20it.%20It%20is%20the%20House%20which%20has%20to%20elect%20the%20speaker%20as%20well%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker.%20The%20proposal%20comes%20from%20the%20government.%20The%20speaker%20is%20from%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20convention%20has%20been%20that%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20will%20be%20from%20the%20opposition.%20While%20there%20is%20no%20written%20rule%2C%20sometimes%20the%20deputy%20speaker%E2%80%99s%20post%20has%20even%20been%20given%20to%20friendly%20opposition%20parties%20so%20they%20could%20have%20done%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20Constitution%20says%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F986229%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%2093%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Constitution%20states%20that%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20needs%20to%20choose%20two%20members%20as%20the%20speaker%20and%20deputy%20speaker%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20may%20be%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20House%20of%20the%20People%20shall%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20may%20be%2C%20choose%20two%20members%20of%20the%20House%20to%20be%20respectively%20Speaker%20and%20Deputy%20Speaker%20thereof%20and%2C%20so%20often%20as%20the%20office%20of%20Speaker%20or%20Deputy%20Speaker%20becomes%20vacant%2C%20the%20House%20shall%20choose%20another%20member%20to%20be%20Speaker%20or%20Deputy%20Speaker%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mpa.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FSTATISTICAL%2520HANDBOOK%25202023New_0.pdf%5C%22%3E%20Statistical%20Handbook%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20has%20been%20elected%20within%20a%20few%20weeks%20at%20the%20most.%20The%20longest%20it%20has%20taken%20till%20date%20to%20elect%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20was%20during%20the%2012th%20Lok%20Sabha%20when%20it%20took%20270%20days%20to%20elect%20P.M.%20Sayeed%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20when%20G.M.C.%20Balayogi%20was%20the%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20just%20a%20week%20to%20go%20for%20Parliament%20to%20be%20adjourned%20sine%20dine%2C%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20go%20down%20in%20history%20as%20the%20only%20one%20to%20have%20not%20had%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20for%20its%20entire%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Indian%20Parliament's%20Unending%20Bad%20Dream%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-parliaments-unending-bad-dream%5C%22%3EIndian%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20Unending%20Bad%20Dream%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feparlib.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F68%2F1%2FThe_Indian_Parliament__Eng.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Parliament%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ea%20book%20authored%20by%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general%20T.K.%20Viswanathan%2C%20available%20on%20the%20Parliament%20Digital%20Library%2C%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elect%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20from%20amongst%20themselves%2C%20who%20presides%20over%20the%20deliberations%20of%20the%20house%20during%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20deputy%20Speaker%20is%20vested%20with%20the%20same%20powers%20as%20the%20Speaker%20when%20presiding%20over%20a%20sitting%20of%20the%20house.%20The%20deputy%20Speaker%2C%20on%20being%20the%20member%20of%20a%20Parliamentary%20Committee%2C%20is%20appointed%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20that%20Committee.%20He%2C%20unlike%20the%20Speaker%2C%20can%20speak%20in%20the%20house%2C%20take%20part%20in%20its%20deliberations%20and%20vote%20as%20a%20member%20on%20any%20question%20before%20the%20house%2C%20but%20he%20can%20do%20so%20only%20when%20the%20Speaker%20is%20presiding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliamentary%20rules%20also%20state%20that%20the%20speaker%20nominates%20ten%20members%20to%20the%20Panel%20of%20Chairmen.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20speaker%20and%20the%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20one%20of%20them%20presides%20over%20the%20sittings%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20members%20of%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20included%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Rama%20Devi%2C%20Kirit%20P.%20Solanki%2C%20and%20Rajendra%20Agrawal%3B%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Kodikunnil%20Suresh%3B%20A.%20Raja%20of%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%3B%20P.V.%20Midhun%20Reddy%20of%20the%20YSRCP%3B%20Bhartruhari%20Mahtab%20of%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%3B%20N.K.%20Premachandran%20of%20the%20Revolutionary%20Socialist%20Party%3B%20and%20Kakoli%20Ghosh%20Dastidar%20of%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Undemocratic%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20not%20mandated%20by%20the%20Constitution%2C%20a%20parliamentary%20convention%20has%20developed%20over%20the%20years%20to%20choose%20a%20member%20of%20the%20opposition%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convention%20was%20first%20started%20by%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20who%20picked%20Sardar%20Hukum%20Singh%20of%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20to%20be%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20in%201956.%20Subsequently%2C%20deputy%20speakers%20were%20from%20the%20ruling%20Congress%20until%20G.G.%20Swell%2C%20an%20independent%20member%2C%20was%20appointed%20during%20the%20Emergency%20years.%20Thereafter%2C%20members%20from%20the%20opposition%20have%20occupied%20the%20post%2C%20a%20convention%20that%20continued%20till%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20when%20the%20AIADMK%E2%80%99s%20M.%20Thambidurai%20was%20the%20deputy%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20opposition%20members%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20appoint%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20because%20of%20this%20very%20convention%20of%20appointing%20a%20member%20from%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%E2%80%99s%20chief%20whip%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Kodikunnil%20Suresh%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20while%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20had%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Thambidurai%2C%20he%20belonged%20to%20the%20AIADMK%20%E2%80%93%20an%20ally%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20Thambidurai%20was%20made%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20even%20though%20the%20AIADMK%20was%20an%20NDA%20partner.%20In%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%2054%20members%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20opposition%20party.%20While%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20single%20largest%20opposition%20party%20has%20to%20be%2056%20to%20have%20a%20member%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20two%20members%20short.%20But%20that%20is%20completely%20technical.%20If%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20give%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20post%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20it%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20they%20have%20not%20given%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20because%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20give%20to%20the%20Congress.%20The%20BJP%20government%20is%20not%20ready%20to%20give%20deputy%20speaker%20post%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20and%20they%20have%20not%20followed%20parliamentary%20convention%20in%20both%2016th%20and%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20any%20constitutional%20posts%20to%20be%20given%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20that%20is%20why%20it%20was%20not%20given%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKakoli%20Ghosh%20Dastidar%2C%20TMC%20MP%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20said%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20%E2%80%9Cmarked%E2%80%9D%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20has%20had%20many%20firsts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Our%20Expectations%20from%20Indian%20Parliament%20and%20Their%20Fa%C3%A7ade%3A%20Observers%E2%80%99%20Notes%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Four-expectations-from-indian-parliament-and-their-facade-observers-notes%5C%22%3EOur%20Expectations%20from%20Indian%20Parliament%20and%20Their%20Fa%C3%A7ade%3A%20Observers%E2%80%99%20Notes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20winter%20session%2C%20in%20a%20first%2C%20a%20total%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2F141-here-are-all-the-mps-suspended-from-parliament-this-winter-session%5C%22%3E146%20MPs%20were%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20so%20many%20firsts%20in%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20out%20of%20which%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20is%20so%20marked.%20There%20is%20the%20explanation%20from%20the%20government%20side%20that%20the%20numbers%20in%20the%20opposition%20benches%20weren%E2%80%99t%20appropriate.%20But%20definitely%20something%20could%20have%20been%20done.%20Since%20the%20provision%20of%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20is%20there%20in%20the%20Constitution%20and%20we%20have%20been%20having%20one%2C%20it%20should%20have%20been%20prudent%20for%20the%20government%20to%20look%20at%20it%20more%20seriously%20and%20have%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20because%20that%20is%20the%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20undemocratic%20that%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20nearing%20completion%20without%20this%20constitutional%20post%20being%20filled.%20There%20might%20be%20another%20thought%20behind%20it%20to%20make%20the%20opposition%20weaker%2C%20and%20not%20giving%20due%20respect%20to%20the%20opposition%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsence%20of%20deputy%20speaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20monsoon%20session%20last%20year%20in%20August%2C%20when%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20skipped%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20proceedings%20as%20he%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-rs-chair-says-wont-ask-modi-to-speak-on-manipur-ls-speaker-stays-away%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%9Cupset%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20conduct%20of%20opposition%20members%2C%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20of%20chairpersons%20filled%20in%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20March%202020%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fom-birla-skips-ls-proceedings-what-happens-when-speaker-is-absent-8873683%2F%5C%22%3Efilled%20in%20%3C%2Fa%3Eagain%20during%20the%20Budget%20session%2C%20when%20Birla%20skipped%20the%20proceedings%20for%20two%20days%20as%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Churt%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20uproar%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202020%2C%20when%20asked%20about%20opposition%20leaders%20asking%20about%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20election%2C%20Birla%20had%20said%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20elect%20a%20person%20and%20it%20is%20for%20the%20House%20and%20the%20government%20to%20decide%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fhouse-govt-to-take-call-on-dy-speaker-election-ls-speaker-om-birla%2Farticleshow%2F78038922.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereported%20PTI.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fvacant-ls-dy-speaker-post-cong-govt-destroying-established-practices-8444786%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20BJP%20sources%20that%20there%20is%20no%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20requirement%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20as%20%E2%80%9CBills%20are%20being%20passed%20and%20discussions%20being%20held%E2%80%9D.%20The%20report%20also%20cited%20BJP%20sources%20and%20said%20there%20had%20been%20some%20discussion%20in%20the%20past%20about%20choosing%20members%20from%20friendly%20parties%20like%20the%20BJD%20or%20YSR%20Congress%20Party%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20BJP%20for%20a%20comment%2C%20and%20this%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20a%20comment%20is%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20also%20reached%20court%20last%20year%2C%20when%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fno-deputy-speaker-in-lok-sabha-some-assemblies-supreme-court-seeks-responses-of-union-states-221491%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20bench%3C%2Fa%3E%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20P.S.%20Narasimha%20and%20Justice%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%2C%20while%20hearing%20a%20petition%2C%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20five%20other%20assemblies%20%E2%80%93%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Jharkhand%20and%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20cited%20Articles%2093%20and%20178%2C%20reminding%20the%20Union%20government%20that%20the%20election%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20is%20mandatory%20and%20sought%20responses%20on%20their%20failure%20to%20elect%20a%20deputy%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchary%20said%20that%20not%20appointing%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20goes%20against%20constitutional%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20can%20say%20that%20absence%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20has%20in%20no%20way%20affected%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20house%20but%20then%20why%20is%20there%20a%20provision%20in%20the%20constitution%3F%20If%20it%20was%20optional%20it%20would%20be%20made%20so%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20But%20it%20is%20mandatory%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20When%20the%20constitution%20makes%20a%20mandatory%20provision%20it%20has%20to%20be%20adhered%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706857239000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02121753%2FGFGx-CPbAAAB7us-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-a-first-17th-lok-sabha-to-end-without-a-deputy-speaker%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Opposition%20parliamentarians%20said%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%20did%20not%20appoint%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20as%20the%20post%20is%20conventionally%20held%20by%20a%20member%20of%20the%20opposition%20party.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-a-first-17th-lok-sabha-to-end-without-a-deputy-speaker%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20a%20First%2C%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20End%20Without%20a%20Deputy%20Speaker%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02121753%2FGFGx-CPbAAAB7us-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20be%20the%20first%20to%20conclude%20its%20tenure%20without%20a%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20in%20a%20development%20that%20has%20been%20called%20%E2%80%9Cundemocratic%E2%80%9D%20by%20opposition%20parliamentarians%20and%20unprecedented%20by%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2010-day%20interim%20budget%20session%20which%20started%20on%20January%2031%20is%20the%20last%20sitting%20of%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20before%20it%20is%20adjourned%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20in%20April-May%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general%20P.D.T.%20Achary%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20has%20never%20been%20a%20situation%20barring%20the%20present%20instance%2C%20where%20there%20has%20been%20no%20deputy%20speaker%20for%20the%20entire%20tenure%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20quite%20unlikely%20that%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20will%20be%20chosen%20by%20the%20house%20now.%20And%20there%20is%20no%20point%20now%20either.%20Deputy%20speaker%20is%20chosen%20along%20with%20the%20speaker%20and%20the%20practice%20has%20been%20to%20elect%20the%20speaker%20first%20and%20within%20a%20week%E2%80%99s%20time%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20will%20also%20be%20elected.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchary%20said%20that%20when%20it%20is%20a%20constitutionally%20mandated%20provision%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20adhered%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20a%20mandatory%20provision%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20House%20has%20to%20abide%20by%20it.%20It%20is%20the%20House%20which%20has%20to%20elect%20the%20speaker%20as%20well%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker.%20The%20proposal%20comes%20from%20the%20government.%20The%20speaker%20is%20from%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20convention%20has%20been%20that%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20will%20be%20from%20the%20opposition.%20While%20there%20is%20no%20written%20rule%2C%20sometimes%20the%20deputy%20speaker%E2%80%99s%20post%20has%20even%20been%20given%20to%20friendly%20opposition%20parties%20so%20they%20could%20have%20done%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20Constitution%20says%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F986229%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%2093%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Constitution%20states%20that%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20needs%20to%20choose%20two%20members%20as%20the%20speaker%20and%20deputy%20speaker%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20may%20be%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20House%20of%20the%20People%20shall%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20may%20be%2C%20choose%20two%20members%20of%20the%20House%20to%20be%20respectively%20Speaker%20and%20Deputy%20Speaker%20thereof%20and%2C%20so%20often%20as%20the%20office%20of%20Speaker%20or%20Deputy%20Speaker%20becomes%20vacant%2C%20the%20House%20shall%20choose%20another%20member%20to%20be%20Speaker%20or%20Deputy%20Speaker%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mpa.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FSTATISTICAL%2520HANDBOOK%25202023New_0.pdf%5C%22%3E%20Statistical%20Handbook%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20has%20been%20elected%20within%20a%20few%20weeks%20at%20the%20most.%20The%20longest%20it%20has%20taken%20till%20date%20to%20elect%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20was%20during%20the%2012th%20Lok%20Sabha%20when%20it%20took%20270%20days%20to%20elect%20P.M.%20Sayeed%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20when%20G.M.C.%20Balayogi%20was%20the%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20just%20a%20week%20to%20go%20for%20Parliament%20to%20be%20adjourned%20sine%20dine%2C%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20go%20down%20in%20history%20as%20the%20only%20one%20to%20have%20not%20had%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20for%20its%20entire%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Indian%20Parliament's%20Unending%20Bad%20Dream%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-parliaments-unending-bad-dream%5C%22%3EIndian%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20Unending%20Bad%20Dream%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feparlib.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F68%2F1%2FThe_Indian_Parliament__Eng.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Parliament%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ea%20book%20authored%20by%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general%20T.K.%20Viswanathan%2C%20available%20on%20the%20Parliament%20Digital%20Library%2C%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elect%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20from%20amongst%20themselves%2C%20who%20presides%20over%20the%20deliberations%20of%20the%20house%20during%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20deputy%20Speaker%20is%20vested%20with%20the%20same%20powers%20as%20the%20Speaker%20when%20presiding%20over%20a%20sitting%20of%20the%20house.%20The%20deputy%20Speaker%2C%20on%20being%20the%20member%20of%20a%20Parliamentary%20Committee%2C%20is%20appointed%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20that%20Committee.%20He%2C%20unlike%20the%20Speaker%2C%20can%20speak%20in%20the%20house%2C%20take%20part%20in%20its%20deliberations%20and%20vote%20as%20a%20member%20on%20any%20question%20before%20the%20house%2C%20but%20he%20can%20do%20so%20only%20when%20the%20Speaker%20is%20presiding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliamentary%20rules%20also%20state%20that%20the%20speaker%20nominates%20ten%20members%20to%20the%20Panel%20of%20Chairmen.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20speaker%20and%20the%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20one%20of%20them%20presides%20over%20the%20sittings%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20members%20of%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20included%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Rama%20Devi%2C%20Kirit%20P.%20Solanki%2C%20and%20Rajendra%20Agrawal%3B%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Kodikunnil%20Suresh%3B%20A.%20Raja%20of%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%3B%20P.V.%20Midhun%20Reddy%20of%20the%20YSRCP%3B%20Bhartruhari%20Mahtab%20of%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%3B%20N.K.%20Premachandran%20of%20the%20Revolutionary%20Socialist%20Party%3B%20and%20Kakoli%20Ghosh%20Dastidar%20of%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Undemocratic%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20not%20mandated%20by%20the%20Constitution%2C%20a%20parliamentary%20convention%20has%20developed%20over%20the%20years%20to%20choose%20a%20member%20of%20the%20opposition%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convention%20was%20first%20started%20by%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20who%20picked%20Sardar%20Hukum%20Singh%20of%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20to%20be%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20in%201956.%20Subsequently%2C%20deputy%20speakers%20were%20from%20the%20ruling%20Congress%20until%20G.G.%20Swell%2C%20an%20independent%20member%2C%20was%20appointed%20during%20the%20Emergency%20years.%20Thereafter%2C%20members%20from%20the%20opposition%20have%20occupied%20the%20post%2C%20a%20convention%20that%20continued%20till%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20when%20the%20AIADMK%E2%80%99s%20M.%20Thambidurai%20was%20the%20deputy%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20opposition%20members%2C%20the%20BJP%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20appoint%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20because%20of%20this%20very%20convention%20of%20appointing%20a%20member%20from%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%E2%80%99s%20chief%20whip%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Kodikunnil%20Suresh%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20while%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20had%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Thambidurai%2C%20he%20belonged%20to%20the%20AIADMK%20%E2%80%93%20an%20ally%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20Thambidurai%20was%20made%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20even%20though%20the%20AIADMK%20was%20an%20NDA%20partner.%20In%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%2054%20members%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20opposition%20party.%20While%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20single%20largest%20opposition%20party%20has%20to%20be%2056%20to%20have%20a%20member%20as%20the%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20two%20members%20short.%20But%20that%20is%20completely%20technical.%20If%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20give%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20post%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20it%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20they%20have%20not%20given%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20because%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20give%20to%20the%20Congress.%20The%20BJP%20government%20is%20not%20ready%20to%20give%20deputy%20speaker%20post%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20and%20they%20have%20not%20followed%20parliamentary%20convention%20in%20both%2016th%20and%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20any%20constitutional%20posts%20to%20be%20given%20to%20the%20opposition%20party%20that%20is%20why%20it%20was%20not%20given%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKakoli%20Ghosh%20Dastidar%2C%20TMC%20MP%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20said%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20%E2%80%9Cmarked%E2%80%9D%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20has%20had%20many%20firsts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Our%20Expectations%20from%20Indian%20Parliament%20and%20Their%20Fa%C3%A7ade%3A%20Observers%E2%80%99%20Notes%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Four-expectations-from-indian-parliament-and-their-facade-observers-notes%5C%22%3EOur%20Expectations%20from%20Indian%20Parliament%20and%20Their%20Fa%C3%A7ade%3A%20Observers%E2%80%99%20Notes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20winter%20session%2C%20in%20a%20first%2C%20a%20total%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2F141-here-are-all-the-mps-suspended-from-parliament-this-winter-session%5C%22%3E146%20MPs%20were%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20so%20many%20firsts%20in%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20out%20of%20which%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20is%20so%20marked.%20There%20is%20the%20explanation%20from%20the%20government%20side%20that%20the%20numbers%20in%20the%20opposition%20benches%20weren%E2%80%99t%20appropriate.%20But%20definitely%20something%20could%20have%20been%20done.%20Since%20the%20provision%20of%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20is%20there%20in%20the%20Constitution%20and%20we%20have%20been%20having%20one%2C%20it%20should%20have%20been%20prudent%20for%20the%20government%20to%20look%20at%20it%20more%20seriously%20and%20have%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20because%20that%20is%20the%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20undemocratic%20that%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20nearing%20completion%20without%20this%20constitutional%20post%20being%20filled.%20There%20might%20be%20another%20thought%20behind%20it%20to%20make%20the%20opposition%20weaker%2C%20and%20not%20giving%20due%20respect%20to%20the%20opposition%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsence%20of%20deputy%20speaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20monsoon%20session%20last%20year%20in%20August%2C%20when%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20skipped%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20proceedings%20as%20he%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-rs-chair-says-wont-ask-modi-to-speak-on-manipur-ls-speaker-stays-away%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%9Cupset%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20conduct%20of%20opposition%20members%2C%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20of%20chairpersons%20filled%20in%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20March%202020%20members%20of%20the%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fom-birla-skips-ls-proceedings-what-happens-when-speaker-is-absent-8873683%2F%5C%22%3Efilled%20in%20%3C%2Fa%3Eagain%20during%20the%20Budget%20session%2C%20when%20Birla%20skipped%20the%20proceedings%20for%20two%20days%20as%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Churt%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20uproar%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202020%2C%20when%20asked%20about%20opposition%20leaders%20asking%20about%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20election%2C%20Birla%20had%20said%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20elect%20a%20person%20and%20it%20is%20for%20the%20House%20and%20the%20government%20to%20decide%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fhouse-govt-to-take-call-on-dy-speaker-election-ls-speaker-om-birla%2Farticleshow%2F78038922.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereported%20PTI.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fvacant-ls-dy-speaker-post-cong-govt-destroying-established-practices-8444786%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20BJP%20sources%20that%20there%20is%20no%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20requirement%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20as%20%E2%80%9CBills%20are%20being%20passed%20and%20discussions%20being%20held%E2%80%9D.%20The%20report%20also%20cited%20BJP%20sources%20and%20said%20there%20had%20been%20some%20discussion%20in%20the%20past%20about%20choosing%20members%20from%20friendly%20parties%20like%20the%20BJD%20or%20YSR%20Congress%20Party%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20BJP%20for%20a%20comment%2C%20and%20this%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20a%20comment%20is%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20also%20reached%20court%20last%20year%2C%20when%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fno-deputy-speaker-in-lok-sabha-some-assemblies-supreme-court-seeks-responses-of-union-states-221491%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20bench%3C%2Fa%3E%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20P.S.%20Narasimha%20and%20Justice%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%2C%20while%20hearing%20a%20petition%2C%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20five%20other%20assemblies%20%E2%80%93%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Jharkhand%20and%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20cited%20Articles%2093%20and%20178%2C%20reminding%20the%20Union%20government%20that%20the%20election%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20is%20mandatory%20and%20sought%20responses%20on%20their%20failure%20to%20elect%20a%20deputy%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchary%20said%20that%20not%20appointing%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20goes%20against%20constitutional%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20can%20say%20that%20absence%20of%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20has%20in%20no%20way%20affected%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20house%20but%20then%20why%20is%20there%20a%20provision%20in%20the%20constitution%3F%20If%20it%20was%20optional%20it%20would%20be%20made%20so%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20But%20it%20is%20mandatory%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20When%20the%20constitution%20makes%20a%20mandatory%20provision%20it%20has%20to%20be%20adhered%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706857239000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02121753%2FGFGx-CPbAAAB7us-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fin-a-first-17th-lok-sabha-to-end-without-a-deputy-speaker%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Opposition%20parliamentarians%20said%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%20did%20not%20appoint%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20as%20the%20post%20is%20conventionally%20held%20by%20a%20member%20of%20the%20opposition%20party.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fin-a-first-17th-lok-sabha-to-end-without-a-deputy-speaker%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Refuses%20to%20Hear%20Hemant%20Soren's%20Plea%20Against%20Arrest%20by%20ED%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02115438%2FUntitled-design-3.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20February%202%20refused%20to%20entertain%20a%20writ%20petition%20filed%20by%20former%20Jharkhand%20chief%20minister%20Hemant%20Soren%2C%20challenging%20his%20arrest%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20and%20asked%20him%20to%20approach%20the%20Jharkhand%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20M.M.%20Sundresh%2C%20and%20Bela%20M.%20Trivedi%20asked%20Soren%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20as%20to%20why%20the%20matter%20cannot%20be%20heard%20by%20the%20high%20court%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-former-jharkhand-chief-minister-hemant-soren-arrest-enforcement-directorate-money-laundering-case-248291%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20day%20ago%2C%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20agreed%20to%20list%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20petition%2C%20urgently%2C%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%2C%20at%20the%20apex%20court%20today%2C%20advocated%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20%E2%80%9Csend%20a%20message%E2%80%9D%20in%20such%20matters%20as%20this%20is%20a%20sitting%20chief%20minister%20who%20has%20been%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArrested%20in%20an%20alleged%20land%20scam%20case%2C%20Soren%20had%20to%20relinquish%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20post%20late%20on%20January%2031.%20While%20leaders%20of%20his%20party%2C%20the%20Jharkhand%20Janmukti%20Morcha%2C%20have%20noted%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20arrest%20%E2%80%93%20just%20before%20the%20general%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20and%20called%20it%20a%20brazen%20act%20of%20political%20vendetta%2C%C2%A0Soren%20had%20expressed%20fear%20that%20his%20arrest%20may%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20impose%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20the%20state.%20He%20has%20also%20invoked%20the%20SC%2FST%20(Prevention%20of%20Atrocities)%20Act%20against%20ED%20officers%20for%20allegedly%20harassing%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFirst%2C%20courts%20are%20open%20to%20everybody.%20Second%2C%20high%20courts%20are%20constitutional%20courts.%20If%20we%20permit%20one%20person%20to%20come%20here%2C%20we%20will%20have%20to%20allow%20everyone%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20judge%20also%20said%20that%20the%20court%20had%20refused%20to%20entertain%20Soren%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20plea%20against%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20repeated%20summons%20to%20him%20on%20the%20same%20plank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoren%20had%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20filed%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20Jharkhand%20high%20court%20challenging%20the%20ED%20arrest.%20When%20he%20filed%20a%20similar%20petition%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20his%20counsel%20Sibal%20undertook%20that%20he%20would%20withdraw%20the%20high%20court%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Sibal%20and%20Singhvi%20attempted%20to%20convince%20the%20court%20that%20it%20has%20concurrent%20jurisdiction%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20noted%20in%20its%20report%20that%20despite%20%E2%80%9Cfervent%20appeals%E2%80%9D%20the%20%E2%80%9Cjudges%20remained%20unswayed%E2%80%9D%20and%20spoke%20in%20favour%20of%20an%20Article%20226%20remedy%20for%20Soren.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanna%20also%20did%20not%20stipulate%20a%20timeframe%20for%20the%20high%20court%20even%20upon%20request.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20going%20to%20control%20the%20high%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20Solicitor%20General%20S.V.%20Raju%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20remarked%20that%20a%20common%20man%20would%20never%20get%20the%20benefits%20of%20a%20separate%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20trying%20to%20topple%20this%20government%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20fact%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706854751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02115438%2FUntitled-design-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-hemant-soren-jharkhand-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20M.M.%20Sundresh%2C%20and%20Bela%20M.%20Trivedi%20asked%20the%20Jharkhand%20CM's%20counsel%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20as%20to%20why%20the%20matter%20cannot%20be%20heard%20by%20the%20high%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-hemant-soren-jharkhand-high-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai's%20Ideas%20of%20Hindu%20Nationalism%20Cannot%20Be%20Conflated%20With%20Savarkar's%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111803%2FLala_Lajpat_Rai.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20the%20introduction%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EBeing%20Hindu%2C%20Being%20Indian%3A%20Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20Ideas%20of%20Nationhood%20%3Cem%3E(Penguin%20Random%20House%20India%2C%202024).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20popular%20imagination%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%2C%20one%20of%20the%20giants%20of%20the%20anti-colonial%20struggle%2C%20is%20always%20linked%20to%20Bhagat%20Singh.%20It%20was%20to%20avenge%20his%20death%20that%20Bhagat%20Singh%20assassinated%20Saunders%2C%20an%20act%20for%20which%20he%20was%20hanged.%20Lajpat%20Rai%20is%20almost%20always%20remembered%20as%20a%20great%20leader%20who%20sacrificed%20his%20life%20for%20the%20nation%E2%80%A6%20But%20Lajpat%20Rai%20is%20also%20known%20in%20another%20avatar%3A%20as%20an%20ideological%20ancestor%20of%20Hindutva%2C%20the%20Hindu%20nationalist%20ideology%20first%20elaborated%20properly%20by%20Vinayak%20Damodar%20Savarkar%20in%20his%201923%20tract%20%3Cem%3EHindutva%3A%20Who%20is%20a%20Hindu%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20Proponents%20of%20Hindutva%20today%20make%20a%20clear%20and%20assertive%20claim%20on%20Lajpat%20Rai%20as%20one%20of%20their%20own%E2%80%A6.%20Interestingly%2C%20this%20Hindu%20nationalist%20claim%20on%20Lajpat%20Rai%20as%20their%20icon%20is%20confirmed%20by%20dominant%20interpretations%20of%20the%20man%20in%20historical%20scholarship%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20325px)%2085vw%2C%20325px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111306%2F9780670094073-3.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22325%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111306%2F9780670094073-3.jpeg%20431w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111306%2F9780670094073-3-199x300.jpeg%20199w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22490%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVanya%20Vaidehi%20Bhargav%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EBeing%20Hindu%2C%20Being%20Indian%3A%20Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20Ideas%20of%20Nationhood%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPenguin%20Random%20House%20India%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20interpretation%20of%20Lajpat%20Rai%20ends%20up%20leaving%20out%20much%20nuance%20and%20complexity%E2%80%A6%20The%20absence%20of%20a%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20nationalist%20thought%20has%20facilitated%20his%20evaluation%20as%20a%20predecessor%20of%20Savarkar%E2%80%A6%20This%20book%20undertakes%20precisely%20such%20an%20examination%20of%20the%20nationalist%20thought%20of%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%A6%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20it%20contests%20dominant%20interpretations%20that%20iron%20out%20the%20intellectual%20shifts%2C%20fluidity%20and%20complexity%20in%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20thought%20to%20evaluate%20him%20as%20Savarkar%E2%80%99s%20precursor%2C%20either%20sharing%20deep%20ideological%20affinities%20with%20Hindutva%20or%20even%20representing%20some%20nascent%2C%20softer%20variety%20of%20it%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20this%20book%E2%80%99s%20central%20aims%20is%20to%20show%20that%20even%20when%20Lajpat%20Rai%20articulated%20his%20most%20robust%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20the%20twentieth%20century%2C%20it%20diverged%20from%20Savarkar%E2%80%99s%20Hindutva%20in%20important%20ways.%20Lajpat%20Rai%20viewed%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20as%20separate%20%E2%80%98nationalities%E2%80%99%20and%20converged%20with%20Savarkarite%20Hindutva%20when%20he%20took%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20culture%E2%80%99%20to%20constitute%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Hindu%20nation.%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20also%20shared%20Hindutva%E2%80%99s%20view%20that%20the%20Hindu%20nation%20was%20crystallized%20in%20Hindu%20historical%20resistance%20against%20the%20foreign%20Muslim%20enemy.%20Yet%2C%20even%20then%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%20stood%20at%20quite%20a%20distance%20from%20Hindutva.%20He%20envisioned%20a%20friction-ridden%20yet%20cooperative%20relationship%20between%20the%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20%E2%80%98nationalities%E2%80%99%20within%20a%20common%20state.%20His%20ability%20to%20see%20the%20Muslim%20nation%20existing%20robustly%20alongside%20the%20Hindu%20nation%20was%20vastly%20different%20from%20Savarkar%E2%80%99s%20demand%20that%20to%20become%20part%20of%20the%20Hindu%20nation%2C%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20Christians%20must%20abandon%20all%20marks%20of%20their%20religion%20and%20culture%20and%20assimilate%20into%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20culture%E2%80%99.%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20nationalism%20lacked%20Savarkarite%20Hindutva%E2%80%99s%20desire%20for%20Hindu%20cultural%20supremacy%20and%20its%20aversion%20to%20religio-cultural%20diversity%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Notable%20People%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Touched%20During%20His%20Lifetime%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fbhagat-singh-jawaharlal-nehru-bal-gangadhar-sarojini-naidu%5C%22%3EThe%20Notable%20People%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Touched%20During%20His%20Lifetime%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%201915%2C%20when%20Lajpat%20Rai%20committed%20himself%20to%20using%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98nation%E2%80%99%20to%20signify%20only%20one%20large%20cultural%20community%20which%20needed%20to%20express%20itself%20in%20an%20independent%20state%2C%20he%20elaborated%20a%20richly%20textured%20nationalist%20narrative%20firmly%20grounded%20in%20the%20notion%20that%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20constituted%20a%20single%20%E2%80%98Indian%20nation%E2%80%99.%20He%20went%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20prove%20their%20common%20Indian%20nationhood%20by%20constructing%20for%20them%20a%20shared%20hybrid%20ancestry%20and%20a%20pluralist%20culture%2C%20and%20by%20rewriting%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20history.%20By%20unearthing%20this%20narrative%2C%20my%20research%20shows%20that%20whether%20or%20not%20Hindutva%20further%20developed%20the%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20national%E2%80%99%20ideas%20articulated%20earlier%20by%20Lajpat%20Rai%2C%20his%20own%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20gave%20way%20to%20a%20rich%2C%20distinctive%20Indian%20nationalist%20narrative.%20Indeed%2C%20his%20new%20conceptualization%20of%20nationhood%20led%20him%20to%20support%20the%20Pan-Islamic%20Khilafat%20movement%20led%20by%20Gandhi%20and%20a%20section%20of%20the%20Indian%20Muslim%20leadership%20from%201919%20to%201921.%20Contrary%20to%20what%20may%20be%20assumed%20about%20a%20supposed%20forefather%20of%20Hindutva%2C%20during%20the%20Khilafat%20movement%2C%20rather%20than%20expressing%20a%20Hindu%20nationalism%20fearful%20of%20Muslim%20religiosity%20and%20suspicious%20about%20their%20%E2%80%98extraterritorial%20loyalties%E2%80%99%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20Indian%20nationalism%20urged%20Hindus%20to%20respect%20Muslim%20religious%20sentiments%20and%20sympathies%20towards%20the%20Ottoman%20caliphate%20and%20the%20Muslim%20world.%20It%20also%20strove%20to%20promote%20trust%20between%20India%E2%80%99s%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims.%20In%20proffering%20reasons%20for%20why%20Hindus%20must%20support%20this%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20cause%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%2C%20much%20like%20Gandhi%2C%20stressed%20that%20%E2%80%98Hindu%E2%80%93Muslim%20unity%E2%80%99%20was%20crucial%20for%20both%20Indian%20national%20identity%20and%20Indian%20self-government.%20As%20we%20can%20see%2C%20pigeonholing%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20entire%20thought%20as%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20obscured%20a%20historical%E2%80%93intellectual%20juncture%20when%20a%20Hindu%20political%20figure%20like%20him%20enthusiastically%20supported%20Pan-Islamism%20as%20necessary%20for%20Indian%20nationalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20book%20further%20seeks%20to%20challenge%20historical%20scholarship%20which%20assumes%20that%20when%2C%20in%20the%20chaotic%20and%20violent%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Khilafat%20movement%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%20joined%20and%20led%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%2C%20he%20elaborated%20a%20Hindu%20%E2%80%98communalism%E2%80%99%20that%20was%20equivalent%20to%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99.%20It%20shows%20that%20in%20the%20mid-1920s%2C%20in%20response%20to%20changed%20political%20contexts%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%20elaborated%20yet%20another%20new%20and%20distinct%20%E2%80%98Indian%E2%80%99%20nationalist%20narrative.%20The%20militant%20Hindu%20politics%20he%20sought%20to%20engineer%20through%20the%20Mahasabha%20aimed%20at%20establishing%20a%20radically%20%E2%80%98secular%E2%80%99%20state%20and%20politics%E2%80%94free%20of%20all%20markers%20of%20religion%E2%80%94which%20he%20now%20considered%20a%20crucial%20precondition%20for%20the%20foundation%20of%20a%20united%20Indian%20nation.%20From%20the%20more%20trust-based%20and%20other-embracing%20secular%20Indian%20nationalism%20he%20articulated%20during%20the%20Khilafat%20movement%2C%20Lajpat%20Rai%20moved%20to%20a%20more%20distrustful%20and%20hard-line%20secular%20Indian%20nationalism%20that%20was%20explicitly%20hostile%20to%20community-based%20politics.%20His%20vehement%20opposition%20to%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20Muslim%20community%20meant%20that%20a%20move%20from%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20to%20a%20%E2%80%98secular%E2%80%99%20Indian%20nationalist%20conception%20does%20not%20always%20involve%20a%20move%20towards%20a%20politics%20more%20accommodative%20towards%20Muslim%20demands.%20Even%20so%2C%20like%20his%20militant%20Hindu%20politics%2C%20his%20secular%20Indian%20nationalism%20had%20integrity%20and%20meaning.%20Grounded%20in%20moral%20and%20political%20values%2C%20it%20was%20not%20just%20a%20ploy%20to%20institute%20Hindu%20majority%20domination.%20As%20a%20Mahasabha%20leader%2C%20he%20also%20remained%20willing%20to%20relinquish%20his%20radically%20%E2%80%98secular%E2%80%99%20vision%20of%20state%20and%20politics%20to%20concede%20reservations%20to%20the%20Muslim%20%E2%80%98minority%E2%80%99%20if%20this%20was%20required%20for%20Indian%20national%20unity%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22A%20Brief%20History%20of%20the%20Radically%20Different%20Nationalisms%20Vying%20To%20Shape%20the%20Indian%20Republic%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-nationalisms-brief-history%5C%22%3EA%20Brief%20History%20of%20the%20Radically%20Different%20Nationalisms%20Vying%20To%20Shape%20the%20Indian%20Republic%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20book%20argues%20against%20intellectual%20reductionism%20and%20the%20pigeonholing%20of%20all%20of%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20ideas%20into%20either%20Hindutva%20or%20a%20moderate%20variety%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism%2C%20or%20indeed%20secular%20Indian%20nationalism.%20Doing%20this%20has%20prevented%20us%20from%20noticing%20the%20subtleties%2C%20nuances%20and%20distinctiveness%20of%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20thought%20at%20particular%20junctures.%20They%20have%20prevented%20us%20from%20recognizing%20the%20distinctive%20texture%20and%20nature%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20he%20regularly%20articulated%20before%201915%2C%20and%20its%20difference%20from%20Hindutva.%20They%20have%20also%20prevented%20us%20from%20noticing%20shifts%20and%20changes%20in%20his%20thought%20across%20time.%20We%20failed%20to%20heed%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20distinct%20%E2%80%98Indian%20nationalist%E2%80%99%20narratives%20during%20the%20Khilafat%20movement%20and%20even%20his%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20phase.%20The%20internal%20complexity%2C%20fluidity%20and%20dynamism%20of%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20nationalist%20thought%20make%20it%20resistant%20to%20easy%20overall%20categorization.%20If%20one%20has%20to%20make%20such%20an%20evaluation%2C%20one%20can%20only%20say%E2%80%94rather%20vaguely%E2%80%94that%20%3Cem%3Etaken%20collectively%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20distinct%20and%20internally%20complex%20narratives%20that%20Lajpat%20Rai%20articulated%20in%20his%20political%20life%2C%20remain%20an%20intellectual%20position%20distinct%20from%20Hindutva%2C%20the%20moderate%20varieties%20of%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20nationalism%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20official%20ideology%20of%20%E2%80%98Indian%20nationalism%E2%80%99.%20The%20important%20takeaway%20really%20is%20that%20blanket%2C%20catch-all%20categorizations%20of%20Lajpat%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20nationalist%20thought%20have%20prevented%20us%20from%20properly%20understanding%20it%2C%20and%20from%20forensically%20examining%20its%20contours%20and%20textures%20as%20articulated%20in%20different%20phases%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Vanya%20Vaidehi%20Bhargav%20is%20Associate%20Research%20Fellow%2C%20Multiple%20Secularities%20Project%2C%20University%20of%20Leipzig.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706854548000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111803%2FLala_Lajpat_Rai.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Flala-lajpat-rais-ideas-of-hindu-nationalism-cannot-be-conflated-with-savarkars%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vanya%20Vaidehi%20Bhargav's%20book%20arg